OL,5, Ambiguous interview questions and      
OL,6, application forms are keeping autistic 
OL,7, people out of work, a report has found.
OL,9,FWhile 53.6% of all disabled people are 
OL,10,Fin work, only 30% of autistic people   
OL,11,Fare, the latest official figures show. 
OL,13,FOne autistic person told BBC News      
OL,14,Fhaving more tick-boxes in applications 
OL,15,Fmight help him to land an interview.   
OL,17,FThe government has urged employers to  
OL,18,F"get behind" all recommendations set   
OL,19,Fout in Sir Robert Buckland's report on 
OL,20,Fautism in the workplace.               
